      • abolish

        public final void abolish(Class<?> cls)
        Description copied from interface: PrologEngine
        Remove all predicates that match with the predicate indicator (PI) formed by the concatenation of the given string functor and integer arity separated by slash (functor/arity). The predicate indicator is formed after resolve the class mapping Prologable correspondent to the given class. For example if the class have two fields and have a prolog mapping to a predicate with "parent" functor two arguments, call this method will be equivalent to call PrologEngine.abolish(String, int) with "parent" string functor and arity equals to 2.
        Specified by:
        abolish in interface PrologEngine
        Parameters:
        cls - class to determine the predicate indicator after mapping resolve.

      • unify

        public final boolean unify(PrologTerm t1,
                           PrologTerm t2)
        Description copied from interface: PrologEngine
        Check that two terms (x and y) unify. Prolog unification algorithm is based on three principals rules:
        • If x and y are atomics constants then x and y unify only if they are same object.
        • If x is a variable and y is anything then they unify and x is instantiated to y. Conversely, if y is a variable then this is instantiated to x.
        • If x and y are structured terms then unify only if they match (equals funtor and arity) and all their correspondents arguments unify.
        Specified by:
        unify in interface PrologEngine
        Parameters:
        t1 - the term to unify.
        t2 - the term to unify.
        Returns:
        true if the specified term unify whit the current term, false otherwise.
